column5: Had a crazy day of early winter splake fishing the other day, and was lucky enough to get it all on camera. Â No big ones, but some wild action out of ultra shallow water!
Smoker going to get a work out, just like you did running back and forth and all around. Enjoyed
Dang. What a blast. Thanks for posting. Looks like you had an awesome day.

8 minutes, perfect. Didn't look too cold that day. I'm freezing and it's plus 7C here today. That self hook set rig looks like it works great. Nothing worse than deep hooking a fish you don't want to kill. Those little buggers sure are spunky pretty too Joeytier. Good going.
